        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Hi friends \xf0\x9f\x91\x8b ,
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Some companies that just feel like they have
         <em>
          <strong>
           it
          </strong>
         </em>
         . It\xe2\x80\x99s not just growth, although that\xe2\x80\x99s there too. It\xe2\x80\x99s a combination of a bunch of good things happening all at once.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2OhSAMhZ9GlgYqICxYzGZew_DTq-QqGMSZ-PbD1cUkTZu2aU_O523FOZfL7Pmo5JOmeu1oEv4eK9aKhZwHlikGwySoQXBNguGBKaFIPKZXQdxsXE0tJ5L9dGv0tsac7gtKQZDFoONcOBAUUHHu2cuDktqpoPwAMIpH154hYvJo8AfLlROS1Sy17kc3fHXw3WKNdYm-93lrDYkGKDCqGDAQktGe9Si5HKUaAYQIijOgUlJhtbMieC1Cx-k2Q3-c7qjWvz-fSDEpV5dLTHNbvxe74Xovmpmp1e1MsV4TJutWDI_P-uC6nU8zJiwNY5hsvSGNI-hGSqrHVwMxaA1Mt0FTDrldpX_RP0ILfzo" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Lithic
         </a>
         is one of those companies.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Lithic, which is really two fintech companies (one B2C, one B2B) under one roof, has announced $110 million in two rounds of venture funding since May. It passed $1 billion in annual processing volume and quadrupled growth on its API platform in the past eight months. It\xe2\x80\x99s on pace to 2-3x again. That\xe2\x80\x99s the growth-y stuff.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Then there\xe2\x80\x99s the less tangible stuff.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Like people. I\xe2\x80\x99ve followed the
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_TLA2UgrBgMZu5huGn2iajYLCcjrcfWheTkCJUpXjvfcERzqWedis7sU-Z6NzQZnzvCxJhZceOdUrRCgW6l4Nh0Q5RaKlZ2qdnRVxdWizVA9l2-CUFR6nka4NzkOxlIRr37NX49KP24IIEDQGc84Kj4chvXXfEhDmgxV-sZ8nIFvsi2vZH__WA73bonT6OulDW9qo4H4ujZj5jjSxZ4CC4FiBAKsE70aEa1Kj0CCBl1IMArhSXzngnYzAyPga-ztDth9_JhZ_Pv6zaXMiXmvLcxj8vt-JyDVq2qd3rkROdE2bnF4x3bLrpXSCmGZudRjVOji5m4wimgVP6jtm49MaAMK3RlGNpW_lf9A8DlIZ0" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          @regulatorynerd
         </a>
         twitter account for a while for his smart takes on fintech from someone who\xe2\x80\x99s been in it, first at Square, then at Stripe. In September, he changed his bio to Privacy.com (it says Lithic now). Or Charlie Kroll, who joined Lithic as CRO after co-founding two fintechs \xe2\x80\x93 Ellevest and Andera. And Nikil Konduru, whose measured piece on
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkc2OhCAMx59muGmgIwgHDnvZ1zB8dJSMgkHYjW-_jB42adq0TftvfnWm4Jzyqfd0FPJxUzl31BF_jxVLwUzqgXkKXjMB8skHRbwePJNcknBMr4y4mbDqkiuSvdo1OFNCitcEpcDJosFZ5yRDPjLGwY2GcpBifCmqrGJW3bqm-oDRocYfzGeKSFa9lLIfj-fXA76bbehD3XqXtk8-0BjeYX2n6GuurZIxxBDnLsSuLNhZY44O676kHEzHnFN0EKpdMpCggQKjkgEDLhjtWY9iEKOQIwDnXg4MqBCUG2UN905x3-S2Gfqj2qMY9_4cQbKOqdi2Ps6t_V7MhuvVaBymFrcaQzknjMau6G9E5SZ9QZtmjJjbB_xkysV3HEE1yELeSBrDp1LAVCs0ZZ_aVPwX_QMy05O7" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Banking-as-a-Service Euphoria
         </a>
         impressed me last August, when he was a VC at Nyca. He\xe2\x80\x99s at Lithic now, too.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         And customer pull. I\xe2\x80\x99ve talked to two Not Boring Capital companies who are signing with Lithic in the past ten days, and my portfolio\xe2\x80\x99s not that big. A third may sign up, too.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Then there\xe2\x80\x99s the je ne sais quoi of everyone just agreeing that the company has it. When
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_TLDtQLX8LFrOZaxiQUskoGCyn4-2H1sUkBFK8VL163-AJp1JPt5Wd2Ofq6dzQZXzvCxJhZceOtU_RCQXmJTvLouuiMNKwtPdjRVx9WhzVA9l2hCUNnlLJVwfnINnsRi2NtqMeQXTGGhlD5BICDxp8sFHfvv6ICfOADn-xniUjW9xMtO2P19cDvtuhd_ps9BzK2qqz4jDT6jNLDjgIbgQIkErwp3ii6pRWRgNIGU0ngCvFpbfByzhYGR8dXyd47kfYyQ8_n5GsulwolJry1OSf2a-4XEKL1bd3PXKis8fsw4LxTkw3uItBP2HG2oDG3tOFS2uwjZkyd8KG5GUtCNs-mnMsrSv_m_4BfIKD3A" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Yoni Rechtman
         </a>
         at Tusk Ventures reached out in June to ask if I wanted to meet a portfolio founder running a \xe2\x80\x9cvery cool company with a ton of momentum and a really complex model/backstory,\xe2\x80\x9d it was a no-brainer yes. After I met with Lithic founder and CEO
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM-OhCAMxp9mOBpgAOHAYS_7GoY_1WFHwWDdiW-_qIdNCLQ07dfvFxzCVOph17IhOa8BjxVshs82AyJUsm9QhxQtU1w_pTAkWhGZlpqkbRgrwOLSbLHuQNbdzyk4TCVfHZRySV4WHI1ji43QSoByihk_yiDBOSp7Pt66bo8JcgALv1CPkoHM9oW4bo_n14N_t4OfdG7UhbK0zJc55emHJMspZ1QzzrhUjHasAyVUr3TPuZRRC8apUlQ6452Mwcj4EHSZeLftfkMX3udAUm0u6EttM1v5_XILzFehmRrau-w54TFAdn6GePvFG9tFYJggQ2044-DwgtX33DRiSt_-GpCnMZyZ9tGUY2ld-V_0D5EPgzw" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Bo Jiang
         </a>
         , I got the hype, but I wanted to double-check with
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMGOhSAMRb_msTSAgLBgMZv3GwahKnkKBupM_PthdDFJ0ya3aW_u8Q5hyeWyR65I_tqI1wE2wU_dABEKOSuUMQbLFNe9FIYEKwLTUpNYx7kA7C5uFssJ5DinLXqHMaf7glIuyWp7IXsmPTUqzE7OYKQaqJqEEoMWYTaPrztDhOTBwjeUKycgm10Rj_rqv1783WqOCcGvmIO7Op-bQqLllDOqGWdcKkY71oESalB64FzKoAXjVCkqnZmcDN7I8BJ0X3hXz6mi85_2aCfFpoxTLjEtbf1Z3Q7bvWiJxjb3M0W8Rkhu2iA8YfFhdscfF0hQGsswOrxJDQM3DZfST7hGozeGM9OE5hxyu0r_pr8EFoE1" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Mr. Fintech Today
         </a>
         ,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_TLDtQyo8LFrOZaxCQ0iatYLCcibcfWheTEEjxUvXqfaMnnEs97VZ2Yp_L0bmhzfi7L0iElR07VpeiFQpMJ_uBRdtHYaRhaXdTRVx9WizVA9l2hCWNnlLJVwfnINnLSo1hip0eDRojJiE9cANamx7FFLpw-_ojJswjWvzBepaMbLEvom1_dF8P-G6HftNno-dY1lYln9--OpYscBDcCBAgleBP8UTVK62MBpAyml4AV4pLPwQv4zjI-Oj5OsNzP8JOfnx_BrJqc6FQaspzk98vv-JyCS2Ua-965ESnw-zDgvHOSze2i4CbMWNtOKPzdMHSGoZGTJk7XwPSDQOIoX0051haV_43_QNljoMN" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Ian Kar
         </a>
         , to confirm. Green light:
        </p>
