         </a>
         when I started writing was about some of my favorites. And right there in my five favorite BT posts and podcasts is one called
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMGOhCAQRL9muK2BFhAOHPayv2EQepSMggHcjfv1y-hhE0InVelU9XO24pzyafZUKnl_Yz13NBF_yoq1YiZHwTwGb5gE1QuuiTfcMyUUCWV8ZsTNhtXUfCDZj2kNztaQ4rVBKQiyGDVIhj0IptlzssBVbzWfBt6roUcm7J1rDx8wOjT4jflMEclqllr38ug_H_DVXqm51XVLszuXtqYAZUMbdrO_KZaP1vrDHaWmDXOTSTBAgVHFgIGQjHasQ8nlINUAIIRXnAGVkgqrJyu808I_ON1m6MoxlWrd651DsompTimHODf7tdgN18to945tbkcM9Rwx2mlFf6OoN9ELzjhjxHd1P9p6cRwG0A2mVPfpjVWvNTDdhJbsU9uK_6F_0aOLHg" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Amazon\xe2\x80\x99s New Customer
          </a>
         </em>
         (and the follow-up podcast,
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMuOhCAQRb9Gdm0A5bVgMZv5DcOjWkkrGMCe8e-H1sUklarU4-amjjMV5pRPvadS0SdN9dxBR_gpK9QKGR0F8hS8JpzKgY0KeT16IplEoUzPDLCZsOqaD0D7YdfgTA0pXgqMKUOLHp4MnGN0ZGbwSjrBhbDgBSUWpHXk9jWHDxAdaHhDPlMEtOql1r10w1dHv1vA797GsfbP7dPtoSQPD8LHx9usR4jzVeHhFhNiaScoaIopwZJQQhknuCc98JELLgWljHk5Eoo5x8woa5h3ivluxNtM-3LYUo179S5tKOuYqk25WbT1azEbrNeiPTy1uh0x1HOCaOwK_mZRb6QXnWmGCLmh9pOpF0ghqGo0ubx_b7AGpShRbdCcfWqq-G_6BwNcjOQ" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
